==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Womanize
<hw>Wom"an*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make like a
woman; to make effeminate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>V.
Knox.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>womanize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: womanize
<hw>wom"an*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To seek the
company of women with unusual frequency, especially for purposes of
sexual intimacy.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> womanise.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>womanizer</ent>⟦br⟧
